Interface RecordReader<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConcatRecordReader, DropDeleteReader, IteratorRecordReader, KeyValueDataFileRecordReader, RowDataFileRecordReader, SortMergeReader

    public interface RecordReader<T>
extends Closeable
    The reader that reads the batches of records.

    • Nested Class Summary

    • Method Detail

      • readBatch

        @Nullable
RecordReader.RecordIterator<T> readBatch()
                                            throws IOException
        Reads one batch. The method should return null when reaching the end of the input.

        The returned iterator object and any contained objects may be held onto by the source for some time, so it should not be immediately reused by the reader.

        Throws:
        IOException
